{
  "texts": [
    "That is, the vectors |Ω n 3 ⟩ and |Ψ n 3 ⟩ are both purifications of the same state on A B c R, with finite dimensional purification space H B R. It follows that there exists a unitary W ∈ B(H n] we findB R) such that W |Ψ n 3 ⟩ = |Ω n 3 ⟩.",
    "Let n ≥ n 3.",
    "Using that W has support disjoint from U X [n 3,|Ψ n ⟩ = π 1 (U X [n 3 +1,n]) |Ψ n 3 ⟩ = π 1 (U X [n 3 +1,n])W |Ω n 3 ⟩ = W π 1 (U X [n 3 +1,n]) |Ω n 3 ⟩ = W |Ω n ⟩.",
    "Since B R ∩ Z 2 is finite, there is a unitary V ∈ A B R such that W = π 1 (V).",
    "We then have ψ n = ω n • Ad[V]for all n ≥ n 3."
